26 Feb 2010 13:57






There's a lot about this one I don't like.

A: Why the painting? She doesn't have any special requirements that make photographing her impossible, and it's weird that the monolithic Foundation would hire a painter to paint her, and not just use a photo.

B: The ability to travel through mirrors doesn't really fit with the SCP foundation. It might work as a completely separate SCP, but it's just one power of a suite on this chick. I mean, you'd think the Foundation would love to find out how that worked, so they can replicate it, but apparently not.

C: I'm generally not a fan of the 'Abel' family of SCPs. They're fine as long as there is some doubt as to whether or not they are who they say they are, but the more of them you add, which all have snarky little cross-references, it removes that uncertainty and just makes the SCPs bible fanfic.

D: Side note: Why does she know about -073 and -076? Biblically, they never met, and pretty much all religious traditions have Lilith out of the picture by the time Adam and Eve start pumping out kids.







