I personally think that the edit to the containment procedure should definitely be incorporated into the article, since it's a HUGE improvement over the current. As far as the changed description, I don't think she comes across as a Straw Feminist at all. How would you expect someone to behave if she were created to love someone, but because she had the temerity to assert herself as his equal got rejected by both her lover and her creator, then kicked out of paradise to live alone for an undefined period of time, then seeing the servile tramp her lover and creator preferred over her, and seeing said trap get said lover kicked out of paradise. I can't help but think that events like those might leave someone a touch bitter. Throw in thousands of years of relative solitude (after all, she can't really have much in the way of lasting friendships or relationships), and you've got a recipe for some serious anti-social tendencies. Maybe it's even been long enough that she's gotten over the initial snub, but still hates people, and takes particular enjoyment from causing other people's relationships to self-destruct. Still, she's got some serious pride, and would thus react far better to respectful requests than orders, regardless of the person's gender?

Sorry for the wall of text.

Edit: Oh, but in the revision, the reference to silver nitrate should be removed, assuming that the mirror-hopping power gets cut (and it honestly should, it seems like a random addition).





